#: ../../../reference/c-api/coremath.rst:217
msgid "Complex functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/coremath.rst:219
msgid ""
"C99-like complex functions have been added. Those can be used if you wish to "
"implement portable C extensions. Since we still support platforms without "
"C99 complex type (most importantly Windows, where MSVC doesn't support C99 "
"complex types as of Nov 2022), you need to restrict to C90-compatible "
"syntax, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/coremath.rst:224
msgid ""
"/* a = 1 + 2i \\*/\n"
"npy_complex a = npy_cpack(1, 2);\n"
"npy_complex b;\n"
"\n"
"b = npy_log(a);"
msgstr ""

